{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6824e133-1860-4b43-840f-dcdc91aa90fa","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01NcduPrCaSCsjVqik5m1VT1","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Providing crash dump config"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01L3d55TCJTaq7mVB7zXv8bD","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"dotnet --version 2>/dev/null || echo \"no dotnet SDK\"","description":"Check .NET version available","initial_wait":5},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Check .NET version available"}],"interactionId":"2065489b-93ba-457c-88de-cfb611cadd5c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to configure automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app running in Kubernetes. They have `createdump` installed at `/opt/tools/createdump`. Let me provide the environment variable configuration and Kubernetes pod spec changes needed.\n\nFor .NET NativeAOT crash dump collection, the key environment variables are:\n- `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` - enables automatic crash dump generation\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4` - full dump with heap (MiniDumpWithFullMemory)\n\n\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` - specifies where to write the dump files\n- `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics=1` - enables additional diagnostics output\n- `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` - points to the custom createdump location at `/opt/tools/createdump`\n\nSince NativeAOT supports crash dumps through createdump starting with .NET 8, I'll show how to configure the pod spec to enable this.","outputTokens":422,"requestId":"2C50:2056C4:168BFBA:197C5AE:69F94C45"},"id":"2d3bf61a-81dc-4506-b6bf-9f56d6ac84de","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:47:58.382Z","parentId":"87bf60bd-10eb-4ecc-8515-330333b6bde0"}
